English
[edit]

Etymology

From Latin present participle belligerens (waging war), from bellum (war), + gerere (to wage, to carry on).
[edit]

Adjective

belligerent

   1. hostile, eager to fight
   2. acting violently to others

[edit]

Noun

belligerent (plural: belligerents)

   1. country or other group which starts or carries on a war

          The U.N. sent a treaty proposal to the belligerents.

